{{Infobox company | name = Korporata Elektroenergjitike Shqiptare | logo = Korporata Elektroenergjitike Shqiptare.svg | type = | foundation = 1957 | location = [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] | key_people = Agron Hetoja (Administrator) | num_employees = 994 | industry = [[Electricity generation]], [[Electric power transmission|transmission]], [[Electricity distribution|distribution]], [[Electricity retailing|retailing]] | products = [[Electric power|Electricity]] | revenue = 20 billion ALL | operating_income = 184 billion ALL | parent = [[Cabinet of Albania|Government of Albania]] | net_income = | homepage = {{url|http://www.kesh.al}} }} The '''Albanian Power Corporation''' ({{sq|Korporata Elektroenergjitike Shqiptare - KESH}}) is the largest electricity producing company in [[Albania]]. KESH operates the most important [[Power plant|electricity generating plants]] in the country. They include: The [[Drin River]] Cascade hydropower plants (Fierza HPP, Komani HPP and Vau i Dejës HPP), with an installed power capacity of 1,350 MW, and the Vlora TPP, with an installed power capacity of 98 MW. The cascade, built on the Drin River, is the largest in the [[Balkan]] region by installed capacity, as well as by the size of the hydropower plants.<ref>[http://rtsh.al/lajme/shtohen-prurjet-nga-rreshjet-kesh-rrit-kuotat-e-prodhimit-dhe-shitjes Shtohen prurjet nga rreshjet; KESH rrit kuotat e prodhimit dhe shitjes]</ref><ref>[https://www.ata.gov.al/reshjet-rriten-prurjet-ne-hidrocentrale-kesh-nis-eksportin Rriten prurjet në hidroçentrale. KESH nis eksportin.]</ref>
By operating 79% of the generation capacity in the country, KESH supplies about 70-75% of the customers' demand for electricity, provides the energy needed to cover the losses in the transmission grid, as well as guarantees the security of the Albanian energy system through balancing energy and auxiliary services. KESH is also responsible for the administration, the proper operation as well as for guaranteeing the technical and operational safety of the power plants it operates.
==See also== * [[Electric Power Distribution Operator (Albania)|OSHEE]] (Electric Power Distribution Operator) * [[Transmission System Operator (Albania)|OST]] (Transmission System Operator) * [[Energy Regulatory Authority (Albania)|ERE]] (Energy Regulatory Authority) * [[Electricity distribution companies by country]]
