{{Infobox Union |name= YS |country= [[Norway]] |affiliation= [[International Trade Union Confederation|ITUC]], [[European Trade Union Confederation|ETUC]], [[Council of Nordic Trade Unions|NFS]], [[Trade Union Advisory Committee to the OECD|TUAC]] |members= 215,000 |full_name= Confederation of Vocational Unions |native_name= Yrkesorganisasjonenes Sentralforbund |image= [[File:Yrkesorganisasjonenes Sentralforbund (logo).jpg]] |founded= 17 January 1977 |current= |head= |merged_into= |office= [[Oslo]], [[Norway]] |people= President [[Jorunn Berland]] |website= [http://www.ys.no/ Official website] |footnotes= }} The '''Confederation of Vocational Unions''' ({{lang-no|Yrkesorganisasjonenes Sentralforbund}}, YS) is a [[national trade union center]], an [[umbrella organization]] of [[trade union|labour union]]s in [[Norway]].
It was established in 1977 as a non-partisan alternative to the [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions]] (LO). As at 2009 it had about 215,000 members.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Yrkesorganisasjonenes Sentralforbund|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Yrkesorganisasjonenes_Sentralforbund|language=Norwegian|accessdate=30 July 2010}}</ref> It is a member body of the [[International Trade Union Confederation]], the [[European Trade Union Confederation]], the [[Council of Nordic Trade Unions]] and the [[Trade Union Advisory Committee to the OECD]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ys.no/kunder/ys/cms.nsf/$all/398645E9A8C3C45CC12574FB0064B7EF?open&qm=wcm_2,1,9,0|title=Om YS|publisher=Confederation of Vocational Unions|language=Norwegian|accessdate=30 July 2010}}</ref>
Leaders have been [[Egil Sandberg]] (1977–1981),<ref>{{cite news|title=Egil Sandberg (obituary)|last=Kvalheim|first=Tore Eugen|authorlink=Tore Eugen Kvalheim|date=16 April 2009|work=Aftenposten|language=Norwegian}}</ref> [[Eldri Langåker]] (1981–1986),<ref>{{cite news|title=Jubilanter|last=|first=|date=3 March 2004|work=Aftenposten|language=Norwegian}}</ref> [[Gunnar Caspersen]] (acting, 1986–1987),<ref>{{cite news|title=Gunnar Caspersen (obituary)|last=Kristensen|first=Dag Arne|author2=Solmark, Arild|date=20 February 2000|work=Aftenposten|language=Norwegian}}</ref> [[Jan Andersen-Gott]] (1987–1993),<ref>{{cite news|title=Jan Andersen-Gott 60 år 5. oktober|agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|date=28 September 2001|language=Norwegian}}</ref> [[Eva Bjøreng]] (1993–1996),<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Eva Bjøreng|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Eva_Bj%C3%B8reng|language=Norwegian|accessdate=30 July 2010}}</ref> [[Randi Bjørgen]] (1996–2006),<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Randi Bjørgen|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Randi_Bjørgen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=30 July 2010}}</ref> [[Tore Eugen Kvalheim]] (2006–2013) and [[Jorunn Berland]] (2013–present).
