{{Infobox Town AT |name=Mogersdorf |image_coa = Mogersdorf-Burgenland COA.svg |state = [[Burgenland]] |district = [[Jennersdorf (district)|Jennersdorf]] |population =1187 |population_as_of = 2017 |pop_dens = 91 |area = 12.8 |elevation = 228 |coordinates = {{coord|46|57|N|16|14|E|display=inline,title}} |lat_hem=N |lon_hem=E |postal_code = 8382 |mayor = Josef Korpitsch |website = [http://www.mogersdorf.at www.mogersdorf.at] }}
'''Mogersdorf''' ({{lang-hu|Nagyfalva}}, {{lang-sl|Modinci}}<ref>{{cite book|last1=Makuc|first1=Neva|title=Historiografija in mentaliteta v novoveški Furlaniji in Goriški|date=2011|publisher=Založba ZRC|location=Ljubljana|page=276}}</ref>) is a town in the district of [[Jennersdorf (district)|Jennersdorf]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[Burgenland]].
==History== Mogersdorf has a famous place in Austrian history because it was here that [[Raimondo Montecuccoli]] annihilated a 60,000/90,000-strong army of the [[Ottoman Empire]] in 1664 upon its attempt to cross the [[Rába|Raab River]] westwards towards Styria. This Battle of Mogersdorf (also known as the [[Battle of Saint Gotthard (1664)|First Battle of St. Gotthard]]) was commemorated by a chapel on the nearby Schlößlberg hill. Having fallen into disrepair, it was replaced by a new building, with an unadorned but huge [[Christian cross]] at its side, in 1964.
