{{refimprove|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox monument | name = Old Palapye Monument | native_name = Old Palapye | image = Old_Palapye.jpg | caption = Old Palapye Monument in [[Malaka village]] | location = 20 km away from [[Palapye]] town | designer = | type = | material = | length = | width = | height = | begin = | complete = | open = | restore = | dismantled = | dedicated_to = | map_image = | map_text = | map_width = | relief = | coordinates = {{coord|22|33|S|27|08|E|region:BW|display=inline}}
| website = | extra = }} '''Old Palapye''' is a heritage site located in [[Botswana]], near a town called Palapye. Old Palapye and Palapye are two different places according to the residents there, [[Palapye]] is a modernised town. The site is located 20 km away from the [[Palapye]] town and the people living around call it [[Malaka village]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Old Palapye monument|url=http://www.knowbotswana.com/old-palapye.html|website=Know Botswana|accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref> This monument site is called Old Palapye because it carries the history of the ancient nature which differentiates it from the Palapye town.
Old Palapye is a crucial site which has many artifacts in it from the middle, late and stone age history. Old Palapye became famous because the remains of the [[Ngwato]] capital which was found in the year 1889 during the ruling of the famous [[Kgosi Khama III]] from 1889-1902.<ref>{{cite web|title=Historic sites Botswana|url=http://www.knowbotswana.com/old-palapye.html|website=Know Botswana|accessdate=22 August 2017}}</ref> Kgosi Khama III initially lived in a village called [[Shoshong]] village and later moved to Old Palapye because of shortage of water in [[Shoshong]].He later moved to [[Serowe]] due to the same reason he moved from [[Shoshong]]. The attraction to the monument includes the perennial spring and water falls, stone remains of roundavels and rock paintings.
