{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Sakania–Kipushi |latin = Dioecesis Sakaniensis-Kipushiensis |country = Democratic Republic of the Congo |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lubumbashi|Lubumbashi]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 40,000 |population = 203,995 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 109,975 |catholics_percent= 53.9 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Gaston Kashala Ruwezi]], [[S.D.B.]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Sakania–Kipushi''' ({{lang-la|Sakanien(sis) – Kipushien(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Sakania]]–[[Kipushi]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Lubumbashi|Lubumbashi]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
==History== * May 12, 1925: Established as Apostolic Prefecture of Upper Luapula from the [[Apostolic Prefecture of Katanga]] * November 14, 1939: Promoted as Apostolic Vicariate of Sakania * November 10, 1959: Promoted as Diocese of Sakania * March 5, 1977: Renamed as Diocese of Sakania – Kipushi
