 |ShortSummary    = La Tremoille reveals to Montmorency his plan to reach an agreement with the English, surrendering the already occupied France to the Burgundy to turn it into an England's satellite nation and create an independent Southern France's kingdom, using Philippe as a mediator. However, before Montmorency and Richemont can be killed, La Hire and her mercenaries attack the castle and save them. Montmorency and the others then try to save Jeanne and Charlotte from Girald, which threatens Jeanne's life to force Montmorency to surrender his half of the stone; however, Montmorency succeeds in tricking him, and Girald dies after having swallowed the stone without the elixir's protection. Once the battle is over, Montmorency tries to pursue Philippe to swear her loyalty to the Valois, reuniting France against the English; Philippe however refuses, claiming that Girald was following her orders to claim the stone in order to fulfill her deceased father's last wish to make her family the next rulers of France, and leaves the castle after having stolen some elixir by kissing Montmorency. Despite this, Charlotte decides to finally take the fate of the nation in her hands, and in front of the entire court she makes Jeanne a knight and the commander of the French Army, with Montmorency as her second-in-command. However, La Tremoille manages to escape, searching the Inquisition's help to discredit Jeanne's holyness and get his vengeance.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber   = 5
 |EnglishTitle    = Proof of Purity
 |KanjiTitle      = 純潔の証明
 |RomajiTitle     = Junketsu no shōmei
 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|4}}
 |ShortSummary    = In order to reclaim Reims and proceed with Charlotte's coronation as the new Queen of France, the French army needs to break the siege in Orléans, whose conquest would open the gates of all France to the English. Since Charlotte has not enough soldiers to send at Orléans' aid, Richemont tries to search for her [[John V, Duke of Brittany|weak brother]]'s help, only to find out that he has no intention to side nor with the English or the French until the war will be over. Meanwhile, La Trémoille returns to Chinon with a letter of the Inquisition, which requires to make a virginity test to Jeanne to prove that she has not copulated with the Devil to gain her powers; however, Charlotte and Montmorency refuse to give their authorization to the test, fearing that the Inquisition might probably use any sort of trick to demonstrate its theory. Plus this, due to a discussion with Charlotte, Richemont decides to resign from her role of knight and leaves the castle for an unknown route. At the end, La Trémoille successfully moves the people of Chinon to attack the castle to force Charlotte authorizing the test; Montmorency and Astaroth try to calm the crowd, but at the end they're both saved by Jeanne, which uses the power of the ancient sword Joyouse to become an Ulysses in front of everyone: like this, everyone recognize her as a Saint, leading to a mass recruitment that recreates the French army in the blink of an eye. Meanwhile, in Burgundy, Philippe wears an ancient cursed helmet, using Montmorency's elixir to turn into a Dark Ulysses.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber   = 6
 |EnglishTitle    = Ashes to Ashes
 |KanjiTitle      = 灰は灰に
 |RomajiTitle     = Haihahaini
 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|11}}
 |ShortSummary    = Jeanne and Montmorency successfully reach the sieged Orléans, whose army is commanded by Richemont's younger brother Alençon and Charlotte's illegitimate cousin, Batard. Alençon however initially refuses the newcomers' help and launches a frontal assault of his own, but he's seriously wounded by Philippe. Jeanne and Montmorency face Philippe and defeat her, forcing the girl to retreat and assuring a successful withdrawal for their allies into the city. Despite this, thanks to Jeanne's influence the French army reconquers most of the castles and fortresses around Orléans, moving Bedford to hire the English mercenary and Ulysses Hunter Gladsale, who sides with Philippe to counter the Pucelle's power. However, Jeanne's supporters quickly get out of control, and even with the girl's insistence (provoked by the fact that the stone is starting to change her personality even out of her Ulysses form) Alençon has no choice but attack the powerful stronghold of Les Tourelles, located on the other side of the bridge that passes over the [[Loire]] and connects Orléans with the southern bank. During the battle, however, Jeanne is tricked by Philippe, who successfully blocks her allowing Glasdale to pierce both their hearts with an arrow made from the [[Lance of Longinus]], another powerful Philosopher's Stone with the power of preventing pierced organs from healing. Jeanne's defeat quickly demoralizes the French army, which retreats almost immediately, even as Alençon succeeds in stopping the English from claiming Pucelle's body.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber   = 7
 |EnglishTitle    = Rain and Memory in Brittany
 |KanjiTitle      = 雨と追憶のブルターニュ
 |RomajiTitle     = Ame to tsuioku no burūtānyu
 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|18}}
 |ShortSummary    = The French army regroups at the Augustines, an old monastery now turned into a fortress close to Les Tourelles, but Jeanne is now in a comatose state for having lost her heart, with the Stone barely able to keep her alive. Astaroth tells Montmorency that the only way to save her is with Excalibur, another ancient Philosopher's Stone with the power of healing any wound. Since the sword is said to be located in Montmorency's native land Brittany, Alençon requires him on this occasion to reach his grandfather Jean de Craon and ask him for soldiers to sustain the battle. Despite the hate between him and his grandfather, Montmorency travels to Champtocé and speaks with Jean, who however answers that he'll lend him soldiers only if Montmorency agrees to marry his own cousin Catherine de Thouars, uniting the two most powerful households in Brittany. Montmorency initially refuses to not break his oath to stay alongside Jeanne without marrying, but Catherine, despite her love for him, agrees to make Jean de Craon believe that they had made love during the night; in this way, Montmorency's grandfather agrees to lend him the soldiers he wants, despite having learned from his old friend [[Nicolas Flamel|Flamel]] that his grandson may be the legendary Antichrist that will end the world. Meanwhile, La Hire's unit is sent to Orléans to assist Alençon, and Philippe too is able to reawaken thanks to the helmet's healing abilities.
}}
{{Japanese episode list
 |EpisodeNumber   = 8
 |EnglishTitle    = Return of the Female Saint
 |KanjiTitle      = 聖女の帰還
 |RomajiTitle     = Seijo no kikan
 |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|25}}
 |ShortSummary    = While La Hire and Xaintrailles protect Orléans, Astaroth leads Alençon and Batard to the place where she had hidden Excalibur's scabbard, revealing to be the legendary [[Lady of the Lake]] that retrieved the sword after the death of King Arthur. Once reached the hideout with the help of some fairies, however, the group encounters the Welsh writer and novelist [[Thomas Malory]], which tries to steal the scabbard by Bedford's order; Astaroth however manages do retrieve it, and in order to counter the arriving English army Alençon orders to Batard and Astaroth to return in Orléans while he will stay back to fight, keeping Malory with him as an hostage. Fortunately, Richemont's army arrives just in time to save Alençon (even if Malory manages to escape), then brother and sister head to the road between Champtocé and Orléans, where La Tremoille is trying to stop Montmorency's troops with his own personal army. While Richemont keeps La Tremoille occupied, Montmorency and Alençon finally reaches the Augustines, where thanks to the scabbard and Montomorency's kiss Jeanne successfully heals and wakes up.
}}
